two days ago.

249
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:24,154
You mean you can kill the carp?
Your dad isn't around anymore.

250
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:31,398
You can't, huh?

251
00:25:45,080 --> 00:25:53,397
Let's remember those who can't
be at our Christmas table.

252
00:25:54,800 --> 00:26:00,830
Let's sit in silence and pray
for those who died in the war

253
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:07,436
and for my tortured friends
from the resistance movement.

254
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:37,836
Our father who art in heaven
Hallowed be thy name

255
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:41,111
Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done

256
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:45,392
On earth as it is in heaven

257
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:47,715
Give us this day our daily bread
And forgive us our trespasses

258
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:50,115
As we forgive those
Who trespass against us...

259
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:52,117
Amen.

260
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:56,717
Amen.

261
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:06,750
Enjoy your meal.

262
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,791
Merry Christmas!

263
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:33,799
Uzlinka!

264
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,752
A crossbow!

265
00:27:44,760 --> 00:27:47,593
- Who gave it to her?
- Santa Claus.

266
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:50,712
He still uses
the same wrapping paper.

267
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:54,719
I wonder what this is, mom.

268
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:00,231
- You know what it is.
- No, I don't.

269
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:10,195
Oh boy!
Genuine Stolichnaya vodka!

270
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:17,231
- Don't open it now!
- Is it from Uncle Boris?

271
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:23,555
The tree holder's from Uncle
Boris. He'll be back in summer.

272
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:29,834
I wonder what this is.

273
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,558
Thanks, dad.

274
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,592
Thanks, dad.

275
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:01,870
Pretty good, huh?

276
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:20,834
This is something
for mom from dad.

277
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:33,037
- Drinking glasses?
- Go ahead. Shake it.

278
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:58,308
We needed these badly!
Ours are already broken.

279
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:03,594
That's right.
Ours are already broken.

280
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:10,910
Did you notice anything
unusual about these glasses?

281
00:31:11,880 --> 00:31:15,395
- They're light.
- This is...

282
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:19,790
This is not funny.

283
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:26,709
Just watch, you heckler!

284
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:36,269
What happens when you drop
an ordinary glass on the floor?

285
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:39,359
- It breaks.
- Exactly. It breaks.

286
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:47,160
An ordinary glass will break.
That's how it used to be.

287
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:52,070
But then a couple of smart guys
got together...

288
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,835
Stop grinning!

289
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:09,037
It's no coincidence that
they all came from Poland.

290
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:12,436
- Socialist Poland!
- I see.

291
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:16,678
Madam Curie-Sklodowska, or
Glass-ska came from Poland.

292
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:20,759
Well...

293
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:28,036
- It's unbreakable glass.
- What do you mean?

294
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,951
It's a miracle.

295
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:35,438
Can I try it?

296
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:39,399
Lida!

297
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:46,119
- How hard can I smash it?
- Go all the way, girl!

298
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:53,074
The glassmakers
won't have anything to eat.

299
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:55,393
Granny...

300
00:32:57,960 --> 00:33:04,513
It means we're one step
ahead of them!

301
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:09,275
- How did you like the test?
- It wasn't hard enough.

302
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:13,557
You think so?

303
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:18,238
Okay then. Go ahead, big man!

304
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:26,358
Who do you think you're helping?

305
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:33,596
The other side?

306
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:43,953
Did you notice the weird shards?

307
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:52,476
They're round like flowers,
and don't cut you!

308
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:57,276
Really. I've never seen
anything like that.

309
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:07,114
This is strange. It's four of us
at the table all year around,

310
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,629
and we've got five of them.

311
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:18,033
It means one try
for everybody, right?

312
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:23,148
HOLD ON, PIONEER!

313
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:27,989
- What is it?
- It's a very interesting thing.

314
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:32,796
I bought it during
a fellowship in Kiev.

315
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,433
- Do you know Kiev?
- Yes, I do.

316
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:37,632
It's a beautiful city.
Everything is new.

317
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:40,911
That's where I got this thing
"Hold on, pioneer. "

318
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:42,519
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

319
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:48,829
It's a toy that makes boys
like you over there stronger.

320
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:51,753
It hurts!

321
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:57,312
- Are you okay Pet'a?
- It just numbs you a bit.

322
00:34:57,440 --> 00:35:03,151
The object and fun of the game
is to hold on. Turn it on!

323
00:35:04,280 --> 00:35:08,114
Turn it on,
grit you teeth and hold on.

324
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:13,796
Why are you shaking so much?

325
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:17,629
Because electric power's
running inside me.

326
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:22,990
- So let go of it.
- I can't.

327
00:35:23,120 --> 00:35:26,476
Electric power's running in me.
The boy has to turn it off.

328
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:31,308
- Turn it off, Pet'a.
- Turn it off for a minute.

329
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:33,679
Turn it off!

330
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:38,475
- Well...?
- I don't think it's a safe toy.

331
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:42,991
I'm a biology teacher, I know
what I can take. Come try it.

332
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:45,315
- I don't want to.
- Take it. It's fun.

333
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,829
- I just grab it. Turn it on.
- But not too much!

334
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:50,520
He can turn it all the way up,
it doesn't matter.

335
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:55,350
- It's not doing anything.
- It can't. We're not touching.

336
00:35:56,280 --> 00:36:01,035
The bodies are touching...
Blooming in May...

337
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:05,678
- Exciting, huh?
- It hurts.

338
00:36:07,760 --> 00:36:13,471
It's beautiful, Vilma!
I don't deserve such a thing.

339
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:20,638
But the gift that brings
the most happiness

340
00:36:20,760 --> 00:36:25,834
is one made by a man himself.

341
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:31,118
That's right. It's for me?

342
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:37,958
Thank you, Jindrich.
Jack of all trades, right?

343
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,752
Is it a dog?

344
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:46,872
- It's a camel!
- Where did you learn this?

345
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:49,594
At camp during the war.

346
00:36:50,720 --> 00:36:56,829
I even made bread chess once.

347
00:36:56,960 --> 00:37:05,390
- From white and black bread?
- No from soggy war rations!

348
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:09,714
You are looking
at the origins of life.

349
00:37:09,840 --> 00:37:15,437
It began here and its apex is
our existence. It's a miracle!

350
00:37:17,640 --> 00:37:21,235
I've got Gott's 45! Come on.

351
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:46,197
- Something really stinks here.
- Frankincense.

352
00:38:46,840 --> 00:38:52,756
Come on, frankincense
can't smell that bad.

353
00:38:55,720 --> 00:39:00,032
- Are you nuts?
- Screwing is for kids.

354
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:04,957
Men will drink! Right?

355
00:39:06,880 --> 00:39:10,998
- Now something stinks here.
- Drop it, mother.

356
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:21,229
I'll show you something
you've never seen before.

357
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:28,113
For God Sake, Bohous...
Stop it!

358
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:37,319
Quiet! Do you know what
soldiers in a trench do

359
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:41,319
when they need to warm up...

360
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:44,876
- What?
- Does anybody know?

361
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:57,235
They... name... bullets...
individually...

362
00:39:57,360 --> 00:40:01,148
- Name bullets individually?
- What?

363
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:08,795
You won't do that.

364
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:12,999
- Marshall Malinovsky!
- Brother.

365
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:22,472
- Dad!
- What?

366
00:40:23,560 --> 00:40:26,393
You're the man!

367
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:39,875
Hands up!

368
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:44,468
I promote you to the position
of poster of bulletins.

369
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:05,193
- Let's have a drink.
- Later.

370
00:42:05,480 --> 00:42:10,793
Let's light the frankincense.
Just for the smell...

371
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:19,029
- Is doing it on Christmas O.K.?
- Yes, it is.

372
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:23,472
You're my best present, Eva.
I'm going to unwrap you.

373
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:28,636
Raise your hands...

374
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:32,199
Bend forward...

375
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:38,196
Come on... sit down.

376
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:46,071
- I'll take your shoes off first.
- Wait. Give me that shoe!

377
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:50,159
Now the other shoe.
Shoes, beautiful legs...

378
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:58,716
Do you see it, Eva?
Do you like it?

379
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:05,356
Take it in your hands
and just feel the energy.

380
00:43:05,480 --> 00:43:08,438
- I don't want it.
- Come on, take it.

381
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:12,269
I'm praying on my knees.
Feel the energy.

382
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:17,072
And now your earring
like icing on a cake.

383
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:25,519
- Isn't this exciting?
- I don't know. I feel sick.

384
00:43:25,760 --> 00:43:27,478
- Mom...
- Yes!

385
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:31,309
Hurry! Turn the light off!

386
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:38,588
- Teacher, can I ask something?
- Yes.

387
00:43:38,720 --> 00:43:40,995
- Does shit burn?
- Pet'a!

388
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:44,029
- What's he saying?
- Does shit burn?

389
00:43:45,200 --> 00:43:50,274
Camel shit does,
for example. It's true.

390
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:52,356
It's true.
Do you know what time it is?

391
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:54,357
- What time is it?
- It's late.

392
00:43:54,480 --> 00:43:58,234
We said we would always
choose dads together.

393
00:43:58,360 --> 00:44:02,069
Go to bed or I'll take away
your microscope

394
00:44:02,200 --> 00:44:05,749
and you'll get it back at
the end of the school year!

395
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:07,677
Don't look at me and go!

396
00:44:08,960 --> 00:44:11,155
Good night. Be a good boy.

397
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:32,875
So I'm being interviewed
for the position of father.

398
00:44:34,400 --> 00:44:38,518
I'm making a nice Christmas Eve
for the incomplete family.

399
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:42,633
I'm making fiction, some kind
of illusion for the boy,

400
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:47,231
a sixth-grader
who is going to judge me.

401
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:53,515
He will decide whether we can
spend a couple of hours in bed.

402
00:44:55,040 --> 00:44:58,510
I came
with the offer of quality sex.

403
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:05,071
Bamboo chopping...
the milk & water position...

404
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:10,228
Long hours of homework all
in vain. All because of your...

405
00:45:11,760 --> 00:45:15,036
- Good night.
- Come on, Sasa.

406
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:20,469
- Don't force yourself.
- I'm not forcing myself.

407
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:22,830
Just be quiet and quick, please.

408
00:45:23,640 --> 00:45:25,710
- Eva...
- Quickly.

409
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:30,479
- Are you sure you want it?
- I'm sure.

410
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:37,718
- You know, Eva...
- Ouch! -Sorry!

411
00:45:38,280 --> 00:45:42,796
- It's okay.
- You make me infinitely happy.

412
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:44,592
That's good, Sasa.

413
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:48,234
- I'll be quiet, don't worry.
- Quiet and quick.

414
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:56,952
Eva...

415
00:45:59,480 --> 00:46:02,438
What is it?

416
00:46:02,560 --> 00:46:08,874
Damn it! I've had enough of
this. This is pissing me off...

417
00:46:10,880 --> 00:46:12,108
Mom!

418
00:46:12,880 --> 00:46:14,677
I will...

419
00:47:07,960 --> 00:47:11,111
Who's this ugly hippie here?

420
00:47:14,920 --> 00:47:16,990
You mean Gagarin's brother?

421
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:42,919
I wanted to pass
the bulletin board on to you.

422
00:47:44,640 --> 00:47:46,631
You bastard!

423
00:48:20,480 --> 00:48:24,155
- How high is it, doctor?
- Higher than last time.

424
00:48:24,280 --> 00:48:27,636
We've got to do something about
your blood pressure.

425
00:48:27,760 --> 00:48:30,672
Two or three days
at our clinic would help.

426
00:48:30,800 --> 00:48:32,233
I can't do that.

427
00:48:33,880 --> 00:48:37,714
- Are you taking those pills?
- Sometime I forget.

428
00:48:37,840 --> 00:48:41,071
You mustn't.
They're very important.

429
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:46,672
Let's have something stronger
before lunch, professor.

430
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:58,156
I have 12 year old, 60 % plum
brandy from doctor Vacenovsky.

431
00:49:02,400 --> 00:49:07,190
- Vilma, have a thimbleful.
- Mrs. Vilma can't drink.

432
00:49:07,320 --> 00:49:10,312
- But professor...
- Her blood pressure is too high.

433
00:49:10,440 --> 00:49:13,512
- I'll drink for mom.
- This isn't eggnog, young lady.

434
00:49:13,640 --> 00:49:17,553
This is a man's drink! Do you
actually know how to drink this?

435
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:27,351
First, you raise the glass.
You can smell the pit.

436
00:49:28,040 --> 00:49:30,952
You have to suck in...

437
00:49:35,360 --> 00:49:37,191
The pain!

438
00:49:46,840 --> 00:49:49,798
Are you trying to kill me,
you bastards? Get up!

439
00:49:50,720 --> 00:49:52,915
You're dismissed! Both of you!

440
00:49:53,160 --> 00:49:55,469
- Well?
- What?

441
00:49:56,360 --> 00:49:58,590
How about that teacher of yours?

442
00:49:59,280 --> 00:50:01,077
I don't know.

443
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:07,190
He's slimy, isn't he?

444
00:50:08,800 --> 00:50:11,155
Yeah.
Pet'a doesn't like him either.

445
00:50:13,160 --> 00:50:16,391
- Can we play that new record?
- You better not.

446
00:50:16,520 --> 00:50:19,193
- Auntie...
- Of course you can. -Thanks!

447
00:50:21,720 --> 00:50:23,676
Will Bohous mind?

448
00:50:25,400 --> 00:50:27,595
Let's have someone else
yell here for a while.

449
00:50:29,640 --> 00:50:31,995
I might put an ad in the paper.

450
00:50:33,120 --> 00:50:36,874
- An ad?
- Pet'a needs a father.

451
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,719
Come on, Eva...

452
00:50:40,760 --> 00:50:42,990
Walk without a hunched back
and it'll happen.

453
00:51:16,480 --> 00:51:18,516
Thank you.

454
00:51:20,680 --> 00:51:27,279
We always have pork with sauce
and dumplings on Christmas Day.

455
00:51:27,400 --> 00:51:32,554
Right, Vilma? Professor
has always had seconds.

456
00:51:32,680 --> 00:51:34,193
I like it very much.

457
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:41,788
- Can we begin? Bon Appetit.
- You too.

458
00:51:50,920 --> 00:51:56,631
The sauce curdled a bit somehow.
It's not really perfect.

459
00:51:56,760 --> 00:52:03,871
- No way. It's delicious.
- It's been better before.

460
00:52:05,160 --> 00:52:08,755
A good housewife
is always unsatisfied.

461
00:52:08,880 --> 00:52:11,952
That's true. It's delicious!

462
00:52:20,920 --> 00:52:23,718
Aren't the dumplings
a bit mushy?

463
00:52:25,080 --> 00:52:29,232
Gnocchi should have
a slightly mushy surface.

464
00:52:30,320 --> 00:52:35,474
Did I hear you right?
Did you say gnocchi?

465
00:52:35,600 --> 00:52:37,955
Yeah, mom's gnocchi.

466
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:42,915
Gnocchi have a slimy surface
and are light and fluffy inside.

467
00:52:43,040 --> 00:52:48,831
Are you sure you didn't mean
mom's delicious dumplings?

468
00:52:48,960 --> 00:52:52,589
I'm talking about
mom's delicious gnocchi.

469
00:52:52,720 --> 00:52:59,592
You mean these true and only
Viennese potato dumplings?

470
00:52:59,720 --> 00:53:01,950
How do you dare to call them...

471
00:53:02,080 --> 00:53:05,038
- Gnocchi!
- Dumplings!

472
00:53:05,760 --> 00:53:10,276
Let me explain the difference
between dumplings and gnocchi.

473
00:53:10,400 --> 00:53:14,757
Dumplings are long cylindrical
shapes cooked in boiling water,

474
00:53:14,880 --> 00:53:19,112
then cut into thin slices
after being taken out of water.

475
00:53:19,240 --> 00:53:23,950
Therefore, dumpling slices
are slimy only on the edges.

476
00:53:24,080 --> 00:53:27,038
On the other hand,
typical gnocchi

477
00:53:27,160 --> 00:53:32,951
are made into little balls and
each piece is cooked separately.

478
00:53:33,080 --> 00:53:37,949
Therefore, it's slimy
on the whole surface.

479
00:53:40,040 --> 00:53:43,032
It seems pretty logical to me.

480
00:53:43,160 --> 00:53:46,869
Vilma! How did you cook
these dumplings?

481
00:53:48,600 --> 00:53:51,478
In steam, wrapped in a napkin.

482
00:53:51,600 --> 00:53:53,716
Well, what do you have
to say about that?

483
00:53:53,840 --> 00:53:57,958
- Gnocchi can be steamed, right?
- Yes, they can.

484
00:53:58,280 --> 00:54:03,434
If you don't know how to treat
your father in front of guests

485
00:54:03,560 --> 00:54:06,358
then get out off my sight!

486
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:08,232
Can I finish chewing
my last gnocchi?

487
00:54:08,360 --> 00:54:11,193
Leave the last dumpling
and get out!

488
00:54:12,000 --> 00:54:15,834
Maybe I made dumplings
and I ended up with gnocchi.

489
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:20,829
It's a disgusting excuse!

