- Where did they learn it?
- Not from us.

729
01:20:59,840 --> 01:21:02,400
- Do they all say it?
- All of them.

730
01:21:05,680 --> 01:21:07,875
Even Sebkova.

731
01:21:09,680 --> 01:21:12,035
- That's terrible.
- Come in.

732
01:21:13,120 --> 01:21:17,079
Hello. I'm sorry
to interrupt you...

733
01:21:17,200 --> 01:21:22,228
I'm running around
but I can't find my way.

734
01:21:22,360 --> 01:21:26,319
You know my wife used
to take care of the PTA.

735
01:21:26,440 --> 01:21:32,675
Where is the high school glass...
I mean high school classrooms.

736
01:21:32,800 --> 01:21:35,792
It's one floor up, Mr. Kraus.

737
01:21:36,920 --> 01:21:38,638
I mean down.

738
01:21:41,120 --> 01:21:43,031
You're on the wrong floor.

739
01:21:43,600 --> 01:21:45,238
I'm sorry.

740
01:21:54,880 --> 01:21:58,555
- Looking for somebody, comrade?
- What?

741
01:22:16,960 --> 01:22:18,837
- Mr. Kraus!
- I'm sorry.

742
01:22:18,960 --> 01:22:23,078
- Are you okay?
- It's fine. I just felt dizzy.

743
01:22:23,200 --> 01:22:27,876
- You don't look good.
- You look terrible too.

744
01:22:28,240 --> 01:22:32,028
I'm sorry. You're so pale.

745
01:22:32,160 --> 01:22:34,628
I always look like this at
the end of the school year.

746
01:22:40,720 --> 01:22:42,711
Did you find the class?

747
01:22:45,480 --> 01:22:47,357
No, I didn't.

748
01:22:51,800 --> 01:22:57,079
I've never even thought I'd be
so incompetent without a woman.

749
01:22:57,200 --> 01:23:00,272
But Jindriska is almost
a grown woman.

750
01:23:00,400 --> 01:23:08,478
- I've always wanted a son.
- I'll lend you mine sometimes.

751
01:23:08,760 --> 01:23:11,115
Thank you. I'm home.

752
01:23:11,240 --> 01:23:14,232
- Can I ask you something?
- Of course.

753
01:23:14,360 --> 01:23:19,195
- What is the medal for?
- For bravery.

754
01:23:21,560 --> 01:23:24,313
- Thank you. Good night.
- Good night.

755
01:23:43,200 --> 01:23:45,555
Hello? Dad?

756
01:23:47,600 --> 01:23:53,391
Fine. You want me to come
to see you in Washington? When?

757
01:23:59,080 --> 01:24:03,232
Life is only luck

758
01:24:03,360 --> 01:24:07,638
Today you're up,
tomorrow down

759
01:24:07,760 --> 01:24:15,917
And then life flows on
to the sea of death to drown

760
01:24:16,640 --> 01:24:20,918
All drift along to the sea

761
01:24:21,040 --> 01:24:25,272
Some today and some tomorrow

762
01:24:25,400 --> 01:24:33,193
And if you find love
don't waste it on sorrow

763
01:24:36,200 --> 01:24:39,636
What are you running for?
You'll wear me out.

764
01:24:42,480 --> 01:24:45,074
I can't go there panting like
this. Let's go see your aunt.

765
01:24:45,200 --> 01:24:47,430
- No way.
- Go ahead.

766
01:24:51,240 --> 01:24:54,869
Aunt Eva is coming, but
she's not coming to see us.

767
01:24:58,920 --> 01:25:01,593
Do you think
she takes him seriously?

768
01:25:01,720 --> 01:25:04,837
I think it's a done deal.

769
01:25:06,000 --> 01:25:09,356
You seem
as if it was today's headline.

770
01:25:10,320 --> 01:25:14,393
- You can't do anything about it.
- Why would I change anything?

771
01:25:14,520 --> 01:25:18,957
She's gonna ruin her life
with that choleric.

772
01:25:20,280 --> 01:25:26,389
I know she's a teacher but
she is completely unteachable!

773
01:25:30,040 --> 01:25:32,315
Do you want me to put tomato
sauce there for tomorrow?

774
01:25:41,400 --> 01:25:43,356
Go open the door, please.

775
01:25:48,200 --> 01:25:52,113
- Hello.
- Hello, professor. Hi scout.

776
01:25:52,680 --> 01:25:55,831
- Come in. Take your thing off.
- Aren't we here too early?

777
01:25:55,960 --> 01:25:59,475
- Not at all.
- Pet'a couldn't wait.

778
01:25:59,600 --> 01:26:01,192
Look what I brought you.

779
01:26:03,360 --> 01:26:08,388
This is beautiful!

780
01:26:08,640 --> 01:26:10,870
- Hi Jindriska!
- Hello.

781
01:26:11,000 --> 01:26:12,149
What are you making?

782
01:26:14,280 --> 01:26:17,636
- Gnocchi?
- I tried making dumplings.

783
01:26:17,760 --> 01:26:19,478
- They're overcooked.
- Yeah.

784
01:26:19,600 --> 01:26:22,592
Let me help you. It happens.

785
01:26:23,520 --> 01:26:29,868
This has Burian's pictures in it.
You can meet Zdenek Burian.

786
01:26:30,000 --> 01:26:31,831
He's my friend.

787
01:26:32,880 --> 01:26:36,793
- Pet'a's so wrapped up with him.
- Me too.

788
01:26:37,680 --> 01:26:41,559
- I've always wanted a daughter.
- Dad has always wanted a son.

789
01:26:41,680 --> 01:26:43,238
- Can I taste it?
- Sure.

790
01:26:43,360 --> 01:26:44,759
It looks good.

791
01:26:46,480 --> 01:26:50,996
It's delicious!
Did you make it by yourself?

792
01:26:51,120 --> 01:26:52,917
It's my mom's recipe.

793
01:26:54,320 --> 01:26:56,709
Why is she there for so long?

794
01:27:00,440 --> 01:27:02,351
Eva isn't eighteen.

795
01:27:03,960 --> 01:27:10,149
She may know what she's doing.
I'm happy she'll live here.

796
01:27:10,280 --> 01:27:12,032
He alone is enough for me!

797
01:27:13,600 --> 01:27:16,433
- This is not right, is it?
- It's good.

798
01:27:18,720 --> 01:27:22,838
- You meant the sauce?
- It's delicious!

799
01:27:24,920 --> 01:27:32,190
I eat everything.
Jail taught me a lesson.

800
01:27:32,840 --> 01:27:39,234
You have no idea...
but this is delicious!

801
01:27:39,360 --> 01:27:43,956
It's great, isn't it Pet'a?
Say something.

802
01:27:44,080 --> 01:27:48,358
The dumplings remind me
of the eggs of Chelonia Mydas.

803
01:27:49,480 --> 01:27:52,313
- Whose eggs?
- Sea turtle's.

804
01:28:02,880 --> 01:28:05,440
- Dad?
- Yeah.

805
01:28:05,560 --> 01:28:07,357
Can I go to the movies?

806
01:28:09,160 --> 01:28:12,311
You are staying at home so you
don't get into any trouble.

807
01:28:12,440 --> 01:28:14,237
I have summer vacation.

808
01:28:15,240 --> 01:28:17,515
You have nothing to do?

809
01:28:18,560 --> 01:28:20,869
I have a date with Jindra.

810
01:28:22,240 --> 01:28:25,437
Then go ahead,
go out with your cousin.

811
01:28:34,440 --> 01:28:41,949
This is professor Masaryk,
our president and liberator.

812
01:28:42,080 --> 01:28:44,753
Soon you'll be studying
about him again.

813
01:28:48,480 --> 01:28:52,871
I'm an optimist.
The West is supporting us.

814
01:28:53,000 --> 01:28:57,676
At least this is what
my brother says. He's in London.

815
01:28:57,800 --> 01:29:04,399
We give the Bolsheviks
one year. Two at the most.

816
01:29:05,040 --> 01:29:06,598
Excuse me!

817
01:29:11,480 --> 01:29:13,038
- Hello!
- Hello!

818
01:29:13,160 --> 01:29:17,711
- Is Jindra home?
- No. She's with her boyfriend.

819
01:29:18,160 --> 01:29:20,993
I see. Thank you.

820
01:29:21,120 --> 01:29:22,553
Bye.

821
01:29:31,880 --> 01:29:33,950
You're looking forward to it,
aren't you?

822
01:29:40,480 --> 01:29:44,678
- It's just for a year.
- What do you mean?

823
01:29:46,440 --> 01:29:47,953
Come on.

824
01:30:24,880 --> 01:30:26,199
Jindra!

825
01:30:32,240 --> 01:30:34,071
- Hi.
- Hi.

826
01:30:34,200 --> 01:30:36,395
- Is Jindra with you?
- No.

827
01:30:37,280 --> 01:30:41,114
- Then say hello to her.
- She's not here.

828
01:31:33,320 --> 01:31:36,835
- Promise me you'll come back.
- I won't be gone forever.

829
01:31:36,960 --> 01:31:38,439
It was beautiful.

830
01:31:43,760 --> 01:31:46,035
- Hi!
- Hi.

831
01:31:46,160 --> 01:31:47,912
I was looking for you.

832
01:31:48,040 --> 01:31:51,191
Elien's going to see his parents
so I wanted to say good bye.

833
01:31:51,320 --> 01:31:55,313
- Really?
- Bye. Good night.

834
01:31:55,440 --> 01:31:56,668
G'night.

835
01:31:59,320 --> 01:32:01,311
- How long are you going for?
- I don't know yet.

836
01:32:06,080 --> 01:32:07,195
Bye.

837
01:32:35,680 --> 01:32:41,038
Come on. Elien will be back
in a year, right?

838
01:32:41,680 --> 01:32:47,710
Meanwhile you and I could
go out. Just the two of us.

839
01:32:48,200 --> 01:32:51,590
- We could.
- You think so too?

840
01:32:51,720 --> 01:32:55,633
- We are almost family.
- That's right.

841
01:32:56,320 --> 01:33:00,791
I can go with you anywhere,
Michal

842
01:33:00,920 --> 01:33:04,469
since we are practically
brother and sister.

843
01:33:04,600 --> 01:33:10,436
Because it's obvious that there
are things among siblings which

844
01:33:10,640 --> 01:33:12,790
are totally out of the question.

845
01:33:47,800 --> 01:33:55,070
- Are you gonna have more kids?
- Come on, Vasek.

846
01:33:56,840 --> 01:33:59,957
Kids, come get some finger food!

847
01:34:01,040 --> 01:34:03,031
- Be careful, Pet'a.
- Sure.

848
01:34:03,160 --> 01:34:04,479
Offer some to everybody.

849
01:34:09,800 --> 01:34:11,756
- Marus?
- Yeah...

850
01:34:12,600 --> 01:34:14,636
London came through.

851
01:34:18,840 --> 01:34:24,437
Eva, that's great.
I have goose bumps!

852
01:34:25,400 --> 01:34:29,188
- That's what I call a honeymoon.
- Isn't that great?

853
01:34:29,840 --> 01:34:34,914
Gentlemen, I read an article
in "Foreigner Curiosities"

854
01:34:35,040 --> 01:34:42,116
that an average woman thinks
about sex every five minutes.

855
01:34:42,240 --> 01:34:45,630
An average human,
I mean a man

856
01:34:45,760 --> 01:34:48,558
thinks about it
every seven minutes.

857
01:34:50,200 --> 01:34:55,433
- What's the point of the story?
- That I'm an average woman.

858
01:34:56,960 --> 01:34:59,315
In that case I'm a woman too.

859
01:34:59,440 --> 01:35:05,037
Gentlemen, I had a patient who
was not yet as old as Jindrich

860
01:35:05,160 --> 01:35:07,196
and he didn't have
a heart condition.

861
01:35:07,320 --> 01:35:12,394
Even the age difference
wasn't as big as yours.

862
01:35:12,520 --> 01:35:16,399
Guess what? That man expired
during their wedding night.

863
01:35:16,520 --> 01:35:21,310
Professor, stop painting
the devil on the wall.

864
01:35:21,640 --> 01:35:23,437
That's reality.

865
01:35:25,880 --> 01:35:31,273
I'd like to show you
the results of my yearly work.

866
01:35:31,400 --> 01:35:35,791
Actually it was
more my brother's idea.

867
01:35:35,920 --> 01:35:39,913
As you know he lives in London,
and we still write each other.

868
01:35:40,120 --> 01:35:45,752
My brother, captain Otakar Kraus,
flew for Royal British Airforce.

869
01:35:45,880 --> 01:35:50,396
During the war he shot down
five enemy fighter planes.

870
01:35:50,520 --> 01:35:55,878
While the biggest tyrants
and mass murderers

871
01:35:56,000 --> 01:36:00,710
have giant monuments here,

872
01:36:01,480 --> 01:36:05,268
Czech pilots don't have even
a tiny memorial in Prague,

873
01:36:05,400 --> 01:36:10,918
but it seems that after a long
period of rule by crude vermin,

874
01:36:11,040 --> 01:36:15,192
even those in the highest places
are coming to their senses.

875
01:36:15,320 --> 01:36:18,676
Hopefully an advantageous time
for our plan is arriving.

876
01:36:19,640 --> 01:36:26,716
My brother and I decided to use
the lonesome pedestal on Letna,

877
01:36:26,840 --> 01:36:29,798
which is standing there
for absolutely no reason.

878
01:36:29,920 --> 01:36:34,232
To make a long story short,
following my brothers directions

879
01:36:34,360 --> 01:36:38,751
I built
something like a small model.

880
01:36:46,880 --> 01:36:48,199
Back then.

881
01:36:51,440 --> 01:36:52,793
And now.

882
01:36:54,080 --> 01:36:58,756
Don't pay any attention to this.
As you know I wanted a son but...

883
01:37:00,600 --> 01:37:04,070
This is supposed
to be my brother.

884
01:37:04,200 --> 01:37:09,638
This is pilot Fajtl. We haven't
made up our minds yet...

885
01:37:12,640 --> 01:37:17,316
Well, compare the difference.

886
01:37:47,960 --> 01:37:49,916
Just to take off, huh?

887
01:37:50,560 --> 01:37:55,076
It must have been
a hell of a lot of work,

888
01:37:55,880 --> 01:37:58,474
and it's such a silly thing,
right?

889
01:38:07,280 --> 01:38:12,115
Don't just sit here like a lump.
Go have fun with the others.

890
01:38:14,480 --> 01:38:17,040
You can't be tucked in here
like this.

891
01:38:25,600 --> 01:38:28,068
Fresh coffee is coming.

892
01:38:29,320 --> 01:38:33,108
- Did you give them the spoons?
- Not yet.

893
01:38:33,640 --> 01:38:37,315
- What spoons?
- Our wedding present.

894
01:38:37,640 --> 01:38:40,712
- Come on, bro!
- It's not the right time now.

895
01:38:40,840 --> 01:38:43,035
Why not? This is the right time.

896
01:38:43,160 --> 01:38:45,674
Why wouldn't this be
the right time for our present?

897
01:38:45,800 --> 01:38:49,236
- Which one is it?
- That one over there but...

898
01:38:51,320 --> 01:38:53,072
Let them open it themselves.

899
01:38:58,080 --> 01:39:00,036
Well, Eva, open it!

900
01:39:13,880 --> 01:39:18,112
- What is it?
- Teaspoons.

901
01:39:18,760 --> 01:39:24,357
A lot of teaspoons
are always useful.

902
01:39:24,760 --> 01:39:30,915
Watch out! They are not
just any old teaspoons.

903
01:39:31,320 --> 01:39:41,275
They are plastic teaspoons.
Light, flexible and pliable.

904
01:39:41,760 --> 01:39:43,830
Here you go, professor.

905
01:39:43,960 --> 01:39:50,149
You see, these teaspoons were
developed in socialist Germany.

906
01:40:22,400 --> 01:40:29,351
I told you to save them.
They weren't made for hot coffee.

907
01:40:40,240 --> 01:40:47,316
I wonder where our German
comrades made their mistake.

908
01:40:47,960 --> 01:40:50,474
There were shooting
in the air during the war.

909
01:40:53,880 --> 01:40:58,431
You two were made
for each other, right?

910
01:40:59,680 --> 01:41:03,992
Anything not from the USA
isn't good enough for you.

911
01:41:05,280 --> 01:41:12,834
If I put two identical
matchboxes in front of you...

912
01:41:12,960 --> 01:41:18,034
and I said one was American,
which one would be better, huh?

913
01:41:18,160 --> 01:41:20,628
The American one, of course.

914
01:41:20,760 --> 01:41:24,230
- Of course, the American one.
- Of course, the American one.

915
01:41:25,080 --> 01:41:30,552
You're like my son. He brags
about America, about jeans...

916
01:41:30,680 --> 01:41:35,834
Why doesn't he get his hair cut
like an American astronaut?

917
01:41:35,960 --> 01:41:37,871
Where's that bastard anyway?

918
01:41:58,640 --> 01:42:04,556
Nirvana, Olympia
And Heaven don't exist

919
01:42:05,320 --> 01:42:11,429
If someone rags on the world
I just get pissed

920
01:42:12,360 --> 01:42:18,230
I don't care about
The infinite universe

921
01:42:18,360 --> 01:42:24,435
I'm fine with
A few great years on Earth

922
01:42:24,560 --> 01:42:34,959
Heaven on earth exists you see
I speak the truth, believe me

923
01:42:37,040 --> 01:42:42,478
For life I'd give mine if I must
but I don't wanna bite the dust

924
01:42:42,600 --> 01:42:47,720
I'm not alone, believe me

925
01:42:47,840 --> 01:42:53,437
There are beautiful things
for those who want to live

926
01:42:53,720 --> 01:42:58,999
Heaven's beauty depends on you

927
01:42:59,120 --> 01:43:04,638
When the time comes
You'll know what to do

928
01:43:04,760 --> 01:43:07,638
When heaven on earth
Starts for you and me...

929
01:43:07,760 --> 01:43:10,718
- Are you looking for something?
- Where are the tablecloths?

930
01:43:29,120 --> 01:43:35,150
Go get Michal to put you
in bed at home, okay?

931
01:43:51,440 --> 01:43:55,672
- Mom! My brother's dead!
- What are you talking about?

932
01:43:55,800 --> 01:44:02,353
- He has his head in the oven.
- In our electrical oven?

933
01:44:07,040 --> 01:44:08,678
Michal!

934
01:44:15,200 --> 01:44:17,760
Calm down. Let me see.

935
01:44:19,280 --> 01:44:24,195
It won't be bad, but I'll take
him to the hospital to make sure.

936
01:44:27,120 --> 01:44:29,270
Jindriska!

937
01:44:37,800 --> 01:44:40,519
- Dad!
- Bohous!

938
01:44:44,040 --> 01:44:46,600
What did the doctor say?

939
01:44:48,560 --> 01:44:51,279
It's just as well.

940
01:44:54,120 --> 01:44:58,079
I'm fine. I just collapsed.
It's not a big deal...

941
01:44:59,840 --> 01:45:01,796
Let's go home.

942
01:45:06,440 --> 01:45:09,750
How is he?

943
01:45:12,320 --> 01:45:14,788
- Well?
- He has heatstroke.

944
01:45:16,320 --> 01:45:22,839
It's so stupid to try poisoning
yourself in an electrical oven.

945
01:45:22,960 --> 01:45:24,359
Sorry.

946
01:45:24,800 --> 01:45:30,272
To tell the true,
he started to smell good.

947
01:45:37,760 --> 01:45:39,113
Eva...

948
01:45:40,200 --> 01:45:41,679
Vasek...

949
01:45:42,400 --> 01:45:44,038
Bro...

950
01:45:48,480 --> 01:45:50,232
Attention...

951
01:46:07,440 --> 01:46:11,149
Marshall Malinovsky.

952
01:46:39,160 --> 01:46:40,832
I read you.

953
01:46:42,960 --> 01:46:44,393
What?

954
01:46:45,000 --> 01:46:46,831
Let me give you my grandmother.

955
01:46:49,320 --> 01:46:52,118
What's wrong?

956
01:46:57,080 --> 01:47:00,755
- I can hear it.
- Who is it?

957
01:47:00,880 --> 01:47:04,077
- It just woke me up.
- Is anything wrong with Michal?

958
01:47:10,240 --> 01:47:15,155
Dad! The Russians are here!

959
01:47:15,280 --> 01:47:17,032
- What?
- What?

960
01:47:18,200 --> 01:47:22,876
Tell them we'll be right there.
Tell them to wait for us.

961
01:47:24,240 --> 01:47:27,391
- What?
- Boris? That dumb ass.

962
01:47:27,520 --> 01:47:31,672
Turn on the radio!

963
01:48:57,440 --> 01:49:06,348
You studied Russian. How do you
say bastards in Russian?

964
01:49:06,600 --> 01:49:08,238
Duraki.

965
01:49:09,320 --> 01:49:18,718
Yesterday,
on August 20th, 1968

966
01:49:18,840 --> 01:49:26,474
the armies of the Soviet Union,
Poland. Germany, Hungary

967
01:49:26,600 --> 01:49:32,675
and Bulgaria crossed
the Czechoslovak borders.

968
01:49:37,400 --> 01:49:40,073
When I came back
everything was different.

969
01:49:55,720 --> 01:49:57,039
Brother!

